<dl id="n25072g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25072g">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25072g"> 72(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Marshal Fo<font color="green">[r]</font>&mdash;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Bl&uuml;cher came to the spot and heard cries from the ranks of&mdash;&lsquo;We cannot get on.&rsquo; &lsquo;But you must get on,&rsquo; was the old Field-Marshal&apos;s answer. &lsquo;I have pledged my word to Wellington, and you surely will not make me break it. Only exert yourselves for a few hours longer, and we are sure of victory.&rsquo; This appeal from old &lsquo;<mark>Marshal Forwards</mark>,&rsquo; as the Prussian soldiers loved to call Bl&uuml;cher, had its wonted effect. The Prussians again moved forward, slowly, indeed, and with pain and toil; but still they moved forward. <small> Edward Creasy, <a name="ECFD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ECFD"><cite title="source">The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World</cite></a> (1915) 407</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14043c" href="c14all.htm#c14043c">VI.C.14:043(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
